			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: accnt splitting my 58 bard to duo with my 66 necro<a name="70491"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Dec 1 04 10:03 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I guess you could just set bard at camp, the wireless keyboard (bard character) next to you, equip a drum (and epic on offhand, if no epic get yourself a string instrument augment from LDoN and stick it some place), and hotkey a Manasong + 3 chants twist, making also an assist hotkey with Selo built in, so your necro can move far away from mob to cast dots, while making it in time back to camp for Manasong refresh, since necro will be perma seloed because bard will be assisting and re-seloing on every pull. 
<br />

<br />
Might want to throw in OOS instead of a chant if the necro is getting resists. 
<br />

<br />
Other than that, I can&#180;t think of another way of bard-necro duo. Pulling with bard is kinda silly, cause as soon as necro snares the mob or uses a high level dot, agro is gone. So you will end up kiting with necro anyways, might as well just pull with necro and save yourself some keyboard hassle.
<br />

<br />
In all, you will be just PLing your bard with necro, since a necro certainly can chain-pull-kill anything without going OOM, and the dot DMG from bard should not come up to more than 10-15% off mob HPs.
<br />

<br />
PoV comes to mind for bard-necro duo (at 58 bard).
<br />

<br />
At 64 though, your bard can get good AA exp on its own charm kiting Hobgobblins in PoN, and Netting Wraiths while waiting on Hobgobblings respawn. And while the Wraiths loot suck, the Hobgobblins drop diamonds and other goodies that sell for 80pp, as well as some Ethereal Parchments. 
<br />

<br />
Bard should have no problems getting in a group, but if you like kiting and solo AA farming, then go for it. Personally I think it is pretty dull. 
<br />

<br />
On the same breath, while grouped you can &quot;practice&quot; Defense skill taking ripostes from mobs, since my guess is your bard is behind on Defense skill. At around 58ish, my bard was behind over 100 points on Defense skill, and I raised it to max while taking ripostes on LDoN missions.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
